---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import { Icon } from 'astro-icon/components';

const personSchema = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'Person',
  name: 'Jonathan Malkin',
  jobTitle: 'AI Workflow Consultant & Implementation Partner',
  description:
    'Jonathan Malkin spent 20+ years getting enterprise teams to actually adopt new technology, including eight years through the RPA wave at Automation Anywhere. He now runs hands-on AI workshops where teams build a real workflow against their own work.',
  url: 'https://builtwithjon.com/about/',
  sameAs: [
    'https://github.com/jonathanmalkin',
    'https://x.com/builtwithjon',
    'https://linkedin.com/in/jonathanmalkin',
  ],
};
---

<Base
  title="About"
  description="Jonathan Malkin spent 20+ years getting enterprise teams to adopt new technology, including the RPA wave at Automation Anywhere. He now runs hands-on AI workshops where your team builds something real."
  schema={personSchema}
>
  <section class="hero-split container-wide">
    <div class="hero-split-copy">
      <p class="eyebrow">Who runs the workshop</p>
      <h1>Adoption is the hard part. That's the part I've done for 20 years.</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">
        Jonathan Malkin has spent two decades getting enterprise teams to actually use new technology, not just buy it.
        The workshops teach the AI workflows he already runs every day.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-links">
        <a href="/contact/" class="hero-btn">Bring a workshop to your team</a>
      </div>
    </div>
    <figure class="hero-split-media">
      <img
        src="/home/workshop-room.jpg"
        width="1600"
        height="900"
        alt="A full room watching Jonathan present a live AI demo on screen at AI Tinkerers in Sao Paulo."
        loading="eager"
        decoding="async"
      />
      <figcaption>Live demo at AI Tinkerers, Sao Paulo</figcaption>
    </figure>
  </section>

  <section class="container section-band">
    <div class="proof-strip">
      <div class="proof-item">
        <strong>20+ years</strong>
        in enterprise technology, focused on adoption across Finance, HR, IT, Operations, Sales, and Marketing.
      </div>
      <div class="proof-item">
        <strong>6 to 250</strong>
        scaled a global solutions engineering organization at Automation Anywhere.
      </div>
      <div class="proof-item">
        <strong>Built and running</strong>
        a daily AI operating system that ships code, drafts content, and runs real products.
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container section-band">
    <p class="eyebrow">Where the credibility comes from</p>
    <h2>Eight years inside the last big automation wave</h2>
    <p class="section-intro">
      From 2017 to 2025, Jonathan watched RPA move from one-off departmental wins to governed, federated programs.
      The tools are newer now. The hard questions, adoption, ownership, exceptions, and governance, are very familiar.
    </p>
    <div class="timeline">
      <div class="timeline-item">
        <div class="timeline-time">2017 &ndash; 2018</div>
        <div class="timeline-content">
          <strong>Sales Engineer, Automation Anywhere.</strong>
          On the front line of selling automation, translating messy operational pain into scoped, explainable builds.
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="timeline-item">
        <div class="timeline-time">2019 &ndash; 2021</div>
        <div class="timeline-content">
          <strong>Director of Operations, Presales.</strong>
          Scaled the global solutions engineering organization from 6 people to 250, the adoption engine behind the product.
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="timeline-item">
        <div class="timeline-time">2021 &ndash; 2023</div>
        <div class="timeline-content">
          <strong>Automation Architect, Strategic Accounts.</strong>
          Designing automation programs for the largest customers, where governance and operating models matter most.
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="timeline-item">
        <div class="timeline-time">2023 &ndash; 2025</div>
        <div class="timeline-content">
          <strong>Automation &amp; AI Architect, Healthcare.</strong>
          Bringing AI into highly regulated workflows, then going independent in 2025 to build full-time.
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p>
      That work crossed functions and borders: banking, airlines, and telecommunications; teams in the United States, Germany, and Brazil.
      Jonathan lived in Sao Paulo for five months in 2012, so working across cultures and time zones is practical experience, not a slide-deck abstraction.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="container section-band">
    <p class="eyebrow">What that means for your workshop</p>
    <h2>The workshop teaches what already works in production</h2>
    <p class="section-intro">
      Jonathan runs his own AI operating system across research, content, coding, scheduling, review, and memory.
      The consulting point of view comes from <a href="/jules/">systems he actually uses</a>, not slides.
    </p>
    <div class="process-roadmap">
      <div class="process-step agent" data-step="1">
        <h3>Understand the real work</h3>
        <p>Sit with operators and map the actual workflow before touching a tool. Most AI projects skip this and fail here.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="process-step guardrail" data-step="2">
        <h3>Decide what AI should touch</h3>
        <p>Automate, govern, delegate, or leave human. Make ownership explicit and keep a person in the review path.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="process-step review" data-step="3">
        <h3>Build the smallest useful thing</h3>
        <p>Ship a working build that proves the pattern and survives after the demo, not a throwaway proof of concept.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container section-band">
    <p class="eyebrow">Proof, not theory</p>
    <h2>Built in public, demoed live</h2>
    <p class="section-intro">
      In April 2026, Jonathan gave an <a href="https://austin.aitinkerers.org/talks/rsvp_f0lg_KSKY8s">AI Tinkerers demo</a> of
      <a href="/jules/">Jules</a>, his AI collaborator system. AI Tinkerers is a builder-first room: live systems and technical scrutiny over polished positioning.
    </p>
    <figure class="image-frame">
      <img
        src="/home/jules-demo.jpg"
        width="1400"
        height="787"
        alt="Close view of a live AI assistant demo on screen, showing Jonathan alongside a real-time AI avatar."
        loading="lazy"
        decoding="async"
      />
      <figcaption>
        Jules running live on stage. The same operating system behind <a href="/jules/">Jules</a> and Knowledge OS is what the workshops draw from.
      </figcaption>
    </figure>
  </section>

  <section class="container">
    <div class="service-cta">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">Let's talk</p>
        <h2>Want your team building with AI, not just talking about it?</h2>
        <p class="section-intro">
          Tell me about your team and what's slowing you down. I'll help shape the right session, on your real work, in your industry.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="service-cta-actions">
        <a href="/contact/" class="hero-btn">Start a conversation</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
